  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Singer. ?] He was then the [GERMAN], artistic director, as well as managing director, of the Staatsoper, which is the city opera of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he was married to the [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Beverly ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Sills ?] of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Her name was [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Margret ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Pfahl. ?] She was blonde and blue-eyed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "She had divorced a husband.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He had divorced his wife.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He had become famous for starting the first-- he was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "He had studied medicine as had-- his father was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "His grandfather was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He became bored with the practice of medicine, and he formed the first physician's orchestra in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And it became such a great orchestra that he became the director of the city opera.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "One of the very, very first things I remember about 1933 is that he had to divorce his wife, and they were madly in love with each other.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, these two people met in my parents' bedroom until the day we left Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I didn't know about that at the time, because I was conveniently in school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But once a week, they met in my parents' bedroom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And if anyone had ever caught any of them, they all would have been shot.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But [NON-ENGLISH] came with us to Denmark that summer while the divorce was in progress.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But Hitler immediately had decreed that this wonderful soprano, the darling of Berlin, blonde, blue-eyed [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Margaret ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Pfahl, ?] had to divorce the Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That was primarily all I remember about 1933.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "People in America think that concentration camps didn't come into being until, god knows when, '38, '39, '40, which is so ridiculous.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first concentration camp was opened in 1933.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
